earn the basics."},"113":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"page","content":"Pairing Devices","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Getting Started"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices"},"114":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-0","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","content":"Pair your phone or another computer with Mate over your local network."},"115":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-1","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#how-pairing-works","content":"How pairing works"},"116":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-2","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#launch-mate-on-both-devices","content":"Launch Mate on both devices"},"117":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-3","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#wait-for-discovery","content":"Wait for discovery"},"118":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-4","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#tap-to-pair","content":"Tap to pair"},"119":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-5","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"What paired devices can do"},"120":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-6","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"Network requirements"},"121":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-7","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"Troubleshooting pairing"},"122":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-8","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#multiple-devices","content":"Multiple devices"},"123":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-9","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","content":"Mate lets you access your desktop sessions from any device on the same network. Your desktop is the server — it runs the terminals, AI agents, and editors. Paired devices are live mirrors that connect directly, with no cloud involved."},"124":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-10","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#how-pairing-works","content":"Mate uses multicast UDP for automatic device discovery on your local network. When two devices running Mate are on the same Wi-Fi or LAN, they find each other automatically. No manual IP entry, no account creation, no cloud relay."},"125":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-11","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#launch-mate-on-both-devices","content":"Open Mate on your desktop and on the device you want to pair (phone, tablet, or another computer)."},"126":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-12","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#wait-for-discovery","content":"Devices on the same network appear automatically in the sidebar within a few seconds. You will see the other device's name show up under the device list."},"127":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-13","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#tap-to-pair","content":"Select the discovered device in the sidebar. The first connection establishes the pairing. Once paired, the device remembers the connection for future sessions."},"128":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-14","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Once paired, the remote device can:"},"129":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-15","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"View and interact with all terminal sessions running on the desktop"},"130":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-16","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Chat with AI agents that are running on the desktop"},"131":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-17","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Browse and edit files through the IDE"},"132":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-18","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Preview web apps running on the desktop's localhost"},"133":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-19","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Send and receive files"},"134":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-20","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Mobile devices (iOS/Android) do not run sessions locally. All terminals, agent chats, and IDE sessions live on the desktop. The mobile app is a remote viewer and controller."},"135":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-21","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"Both devices must be on the **same local network** (same Wi-Fi or LAN)"},"136":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-22","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"Mate uses TCP port **53317** by default for communication (configurable in Settings)"},"137":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-23","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"Multicast UDP must not be blocked by your router — most home and office networks allow it"},"138":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-24","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"No internet connection is required for pairing"},"139":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-25","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"If devices don't discover each other:"},"140":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-26","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"Confirm both devices are on the same Wi-Fi network"},"141":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-27","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/g