) / `Ctrl + ,` (Windows/Linux)."},"532":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-20","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#port","content":"The TCP port Mate uses for device communication. Default is **53317**. Change this if the default port conflicts with another application. All paired devices must use the same port."},"533":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-21","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#theme","content":"Choose between light, dark, or system theme. System follows your OS appearance setting."},"534":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-22","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#language","content":"Mate supports multiple interface languages. The default follows your system language."},"535":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-23","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#default-shell","content":"The shell used for new terminal sessions. Mate detects your system's default shell automatically (e.g., zsh on macOS, bash on Linux). You can override this to use a different shell."},"536":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-24","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#font-size","content":"The terminal font size in points. Adjustable via settings or with keyboard shortcuts (`Cmd + =` / `Cmd + -`)."},"537":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-25","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#scrollback-buffer","content":"The number of lines kept in the terminal's scrollback history. Higher values use more memory but let you scroll back further through command output."},"538":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-26","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#enabled-connectors","content":"Toggle individual MCP connectors on or off. Each connector shows its name, category, and connection status."},"539":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-27","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#credentials","content":"Manage API keys and tokens for connectors. Credentials are stored in platform-native secure storage (Keychain on macOS, Credential Manager on Windows, Secret Service on Linux)."},"540":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-28","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#command-verification","content":"Mate checks that the required command for each connector (usually `npx`) is available before enabling it. If a command is not found, Mate shows installation guidance."},"541":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-29","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#device-name","content":"The name other devices see when they discover your device on the network. Defaults to your computer's hostname."},"542":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-30","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#auto-discovery","content":"Toggle multicast UDP discovery on or off. When enabled, Mate automatically finds other devices on the same network. When disabled, you need to connect manually."},"543":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-31","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#default-cli","content":"The AI CLI to use when creating new agent chat sessions. Options depend on which CLIs are installed on your system (Claude Code, Codex, Copilot)."},"544":{"id":"/docs/reference/settings-32","page_id":"/docs/reference/settings","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/settings#mcp-config-generation","content":"Mate automatically generates MCP configuration files that agent CLIs read at startup. This section shows which connectors will be passed to agent sessions and lets you configure additional