","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"The process stays alive for the entire conversation — follow-up messages go through stdin"},"563":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-16","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"Responses stream back in real time with text, tool calls, and results"},"564":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-17","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"MCP connectors are passed via a generated config file"},"565":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-18","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#how-it-works","content":"This long-lived process model means there is no multi-second delay between messages. After the initial startup, follow-ups are instant."},"566":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-19","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#requirements","content":"You need the Claude Code CLI installed on your system:"},"567":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-20","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#requirements","content":"Mate detects available CLIs automatically. If `claude` is in your PATH, it appears as an option when creating an agent chat."},"568":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-21","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#streaming-responses","content":"Text and tool use stream in real time. You see the agent's thinking as it happens, not just the final result."},"569":{"id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code-22","page_id":"/docs/integrations/claude-code","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/integrations/claude-code#tool-use-visualization","content":"When Claude Code c